data.meta_description:
8,086 likes, 149 comments - firstladyofsong on June 15, 2024: "On June 15, 1996, Ella Fitzgerald succumbed to complications of Diabetes.  She was 79 years old.  A jazz trio was playing softly as she slipped away.  Ella, your music will always be a blessing.  She was laid to rest in a private ceremony at Inglewood Park Cemetery, in the Los Angeles area.  Fans from around the world visit to pay their respects and leave flowers and tokens of affection (like her records!).

https://open.spotify.com/track/4dRsNHZdFTtYKDh05EyfJw?si=2b7a1db29bc34a8f".
